# Privacy Policy

Last updated: January 7, 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how information is collected, used, stored, and protected when interacting with our AI-powered voice agent (“Voice Agent”).

By using or interacting with the Voice Agent, you consent to the practices described in this policy.

---

## 1. Information We Collect

The Voice Agent may collect the following types of information during phone calls or voice interactions:

- Caller phone number
- Caller name (if voluntarily provided)
- Voice recordings and transcriptions
- Call metadata (date, time, duration)
- Information voluntarily shared by the caller, such as:
  - Reason for the call
  - Service requests
  - Location details
  - Contact details (email, phone number)
  - Emergency-related information when applicable

The Voice Agent only collects information necessary to fulfill its intended purpose.

---

## 2. How We Use Information

Collected information may be used to:

- Answer and route incoming calls
- Qualify service requests
- Detect emergencies or urgent situations
- Schedule callbacks or appointments
- Send follow-up messages (SMS or call-back notifications)
- Improve system performance and reliability
- Ensure service quality, security, and compliance

We do not use collected data for unrelated purposes.

---

## 3. Call Recording & AI Processing

Calls may be recorded and processed by artificial intelligence systems to:

- Understand speech
- Generate responses
- Extract relevant context
- Assist with routing and follow-ups

Recordings and transcriptions may be temporarily stored for operational, quality, or compliance purposes.

---

## 4. Data Sharing

We do not sell personal data.

Information may be shared only with:

- Authorized service providers involved in operating the Voice Agent (telephony, AI processing, messaging)
- Business operators receiving the call or service request
- Legal authorities if required by law

All third-party providers are required to follow appropriate data protection and confidentiality standards.

---

## 5. Data Retention

Personal data is retained only for as long as necessary to:

- Complete the intended service
- Meet operational or legal requirements
- Resolve disputes or issues

Data may be deleted or anonymized after this period.

---

## 6. Data Security

We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect personal data against:

- Unauthorized access
- Loss
- Misuse
- Disclosure

However, no system can guarantee absolute security.

---

## 7. Your Rights (Canada / Québec)

Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to:

- Access your personal data
- Request correction of inaccurate data
- Request deletion of personal data
- Withdraw consent where applicable

Requests can be made using the contact information below.

---

## 8. Children’s Privacy

The Voice Agent is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13.  
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

---

## 9. Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time.  
Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date.

---

## 10. Contact Information

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or data handling practices, please contact:

Email: ai@obscyro.com

---

By interacting with the Voice Agent, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy.
